-- Sandy Casar Wins Alpine Stage at Tour de France as Andy Schleck Takes Lead
-- Alex Duff
-- 2010-07-13T15:16:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/sandy-casar-wins-alpine-stage-at-tour-de-france-as-andy-schleck-takes-lead.html

          
          
             Sandy Casar won stage nine of the
Tour de France in the Alps. Andy Schleck took over the race-
leading yellow jersey from Cadel Evans.  
 Evans struggled on the 2,000-meter Col de la Madeleine
mountain near the end of the 127-mile ride.  
          
          


  


        